 The Golden Rule of Binary (MSB is King)
In binary, a single bit is strictly greater than the sum of all bits to its right. (2^k > sum of {i=0 to k-1} 2^i).
How to use it: Whenever a problem asks you to minimize or maximize a bitwise value, always iterate from left to right 
(from the 60th bit down to the 0th bit).The moment you can safely turn on a high bit, do it.
It doesn't matter if it ruins every single smaller bit; the math guarantees you still come out ahead.
